ition, secure Varoma lid and cook for a further <b>2-4 min\/Varoma\/speed 4<b> or until potatoes, salmon and beans are cooked to your liking (see Tips). Transfer into a large bowl to cool. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place eschalot and anchovy fillets into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add sugar, mustard, lemon juice and oil and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 6<b>. Season with salt and pepper to taste."},{"content":"When eggs are cool enough to handle, peel and cut into halves. Flake reserved salmon and add to large bowl with potatoes and beans. Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh tomatoes and olives into it, transfer into large bowl. Add spring onions\/shallots and eggs. Add Anchovy dressing to bowl, toss gently to combine, then serve."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Using cold eggs from the refrigerator will increase cooking time. We used X-Large eggs (59 g) in this recipe; using smaller eggs will reduce the cooking time. Please refer to The Basic Cookbook for timings for both soft and hard boiled eggs. Take care when peeling soft boiled eggs.","Cooking times may vary according to the thickness of the salmon fillets."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","35m","4 portions"]}